articles.headline: Which players could make a move at the MLB deadline?
articles.description: Xavier Scruggs names the players he believes could be up for grabs at the MLB trade deadline.

articles.headline: Ohtani strikes out two, but Dodgers stick to one-inning plan
articles.description: Shohei Ohtani recorded his first two strikeouts in a scoreless first inning but didn't return for the second despite throwing only 18 pitches.

articles.headline: OF Jarren Duran, manager Alex Cora ejected at San Francisco
articles.description: Red Sox outfielder Jarren Duran and manager Alex Cora were ejected in Sunday's series finale against the Giants.

articles.headline: Dubón hits 2 homers and Hader retires Trout to save Astros' 8-7 win over Angels
articles.description: — Mauricio Dubón homered twice and Josh Hader stayed perfect in 19 save chances this season by getting Mike Trout to line out to center field with a runner on second as the Houston Astros held off the Los Angeles Angels 8-7 in the rubber game of their...

articles.headline: Jose Iglesias drives in winning run for Padres
articles.description: Luis Arraez beats the throw home to give the Padres a 3-2 win over the Royals in the bottom of the 9th inning.

articles.headline: Slade Cecconi pitches Guardians to 3-0 win over Athletics
articles.description: — Slade Cecconi pitched a career-high seven innings and Emmanuel Clase escaped a bases-loaded jam in the ninth to lead the Cleveland Guardians to a 3-0 victory over the Athletics in the rubber game of their series Sunday.
